-- Acta Raises $3.4 Million to Fund Hydrogen Development
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   M a r t i n
-- 2012-12-24T14:20:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-24/acta-raises-3-4-million-to-fund-hydrogen-development.html
Acta SpA (ACTA) , an Italian clean-energy
developer, raised 2.1 million pounds ($3.4 million) by selling
shares to fund an expansion of its hydrogen production capacity.  Acta issued 42.2 million ordinary shares at a price of 5
pence a share, the Pisa-based company said in a statement today.
Acta fell 7.8 percent to 5.88 pence in London today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
